attachments.text: Meet the Top 8 finalists for the Great Designer Search 3!
attachments.fallback: MAGIC: THE GATHERING: Great Designer Search 3 – Meet the Top 8

text: FOr those of you who did the quizes, they give you the answers if you saved your own.
Hrm…I’m reading some of the submissions from the first guy, Alex, and the wording is very klunky.
the saheeli one is pretty not great
His seem overly complex
Goblin guillotine seemed funny at first, then I got bored at quit caring behind the wall of text
It'll be great for Un-Bearable though!
Right - the wording is waaay too dense. It’s like he misses Ice Age design…

Well, the second guy Ari has bulk mythic design down pat:

Mugai Creation Saga (mythic rare)
5GGUU
Sorcery
Do both of these, in either order -
* Draw a card for each creature you control.
* Create a 2/2 green Bear creature token for each card in your hand.
jesus that is an expensive cost
So far a lot of designers seem to think complexity == good game play…
Basically everyone who wants Future Sight 2
Which kinda makes sense
I'd be down with FS2, and I can see why people who are wanna be designers
MtG doesn’t see more complexity in the designs.

If violence isn't the answer, you're asking the wrong question.
~Tibalt
That's great flavor txt
yeah…that is pretty fantastic….he’s better with the flavor text than the cards…which is the wrong skill required here.
They've hired people from the GDS into other slots before so who knows
I’m really liking Jeremy Geist’s designs. They’re fun and make fairly clear.

Whimsical Djinn (mythic rare)
4UR
Creature — Djinn
4/4
Flying
At the beginning of your upkeep, choose one at random that hasn’t been chosen. If you can’t, return Whimsical Djinn to its owner’s hand.
– Whimsical Djinn deals 4 damage to each of up to two target creatures and/or planeswalkers.
– Whimsical Djinn gains double strike until end of turn.
– Draw three cards.
for sure, I actually like his the best so far

Mama Bear (common)
2(g/w)
Creature — Bear
3/2
Mama Bear enters the battlefield with a +1/+1 counter on it if you control a creature with power 1 or less.
I also like that he doesn’t take naming the cards too seriously like some fo the others
Yeah…this is sweet, actually…

Sign In Someone Else’s Blood (common)
BR
Instant
Sign In Someone Else’s Blood deals 3 damage to target creature you control.
Draw two cards.
Scott Wilson impressed me most. His designs had me engaged, brewing, and even giggling a little. Very elegant work
Haven’t gotten that far yet.
oh man, trash recycler, I read as “trash rare” first
He’s obviously pandering to MaRo with the pun names…

Tomarin Blair, Lord of Time (mythic rare)
2WU
Planeswalker - Tomarin
4
+1: After this main phase, there is an additional upkeep step, followed by an additional main phase.
-3: Target opponent skips his or her next combat phase.
-8: Create a colorless Paradox artifact token with T, Sacrifice this artifact: End the turn.

This is a little slice of ‘no’:
Oasis Mirage (mythic rare)
4GU
Legendary Enchantment
You may have lands you play enter the battlefield as a copy of any permanent on the battlefield.
for sure, that would be forever busted
On the surface it’s stupid busted
in UG commander it would just be dumb and dumb all games with it out
It’s the type of thing wotc would totally do
No…
only costs six too
I could see it if it was a creature that did it
God…the complexity of maintaining the board state…which lands are which permanent? Ugh…
You already have that with Clone Legion
thats not too bad, because you arne’t using lands to be creatues
Which is only creatures, so they’re just tokens, these are lands that aren’t lands necessarily but other things.
Also clone legion costs 9
It’s just waay too powerful of an effect for too little cost in colors that can absolutely abuse it.
If they did that until end of turn, that’d be one thing.
Their main challenge should have been "make an interesting boros 5 drop..."
Make something busted and call it Simic and nobody bats an eye. Make it a challenge and do it in RW

It's not really about whether it's busted. It's a natural place for Simic to go. They have Infinite Reflection and Clone Legion and Essence of the Wild. If mana cost is the issue, crank it higher. The idea itself is solid and this is a contest of ideas. 
Also his Boros card is pretty sick. (Dumb name though)
it was called come at me bros, but I once again read it as come at me boros
That was the Gruul card
still fits

Easily Excitea-Bull (rare)
2RW
Creature - Beast
2/2
Haste, lifelink
Whenever a player’s life total changes, put a +1/+1 counter on CARDNAME.
Maybe if it had first strike...
These are good keywords for it. First turn it drops it becomes a 4/4. Lifelink is a very good touch
They ain't looking for cards commander players will like for all these designs. They want to see something inventive but that also respects the color pie
Sure, but making a busted Simic card doesn’t take that much innovation…all you have to do is respect the color pie.
Which is why I said it feels like something WotC would do :stuck_out_tongue_winking_eye:
Sure, but encouraging them to make more goodstuff cards for Simic shouldn’t be encouraged.
I'm just saying, keep you eye on him. I'll be genuinely shocked if he doesn't make it to top 3
I sure hope one of the female finalists makes the top 3! Ohhhh…wait a minute…

I did like this mixing of modal and x spells:
Cranky Hydra (rare)
XRG
Creature — Hydra
1/1
When Cranky Hydra enters the battlefield, choose X. You may choose the same mode more than once —
* Put a +1/+1 counter on Cranky Hydra.
* Cranky Hydra deals 1 damage to target player.
* Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
(If I may throw shade, I'll also be shocked if Linus and Alex aren't the first to leave. They have ambitious stuff too, but much of it is tough to grok)
I love modal spells. Escalate was one of my favorite kicker variant in a hot minute
Especially when they played around with the alternate costs w/ Collective Brutality
That card gets me all...twitchy
Anyone watch the Magicians?
Nope. Looked like a Twilight meets Harry Potter abomination.
It does look like that
And the first season is a bit rough just because nearly every character is kind of an insufferable asshole
But that kind of became a plot point where they had to learn to stop being insufferable assholes, and it's gotten really quite excellent
There was a bit last night were a solution to a problem was all the main characters singing Under Pressure that should have been absolute bullshit and somehow it really worked
You aren’t winning me over...:thinking_face:
Yeah it's a hard sell
It's just been one of those shows that consistently surprised me after a soft start, a la Fringe
<@U3RJ9VDRT> what about Collective Brutality makes you twitchy? My God…it’s a $22 dollar card? I probably have some in a binder somewhere…
wasn’t me who get twitchy
I mean <@U4BFDSLKT>…you just got in the way, <@U3RJ9VDRT>
it’s just because I’m always on your mind Henry
can’t help that my butt just won’t stop
can’t stop/won’t stop…
It gets me twitchy because the little modern I play is typically burn and that card is just a huge blow out
Modern is a silly format…
Agreed
I play a handful of times a year
It’s fun, but I just don’t get the required reps to do anything except jack around
That's why I put together bogles. Relatively cheap by modern standards and requires little skill or understanding of anything happening around you
you just do your thing and hope no one can interact
Yep, which is perfect for someone who plays on a whim like two times a year
What’s a whole Boggles deck run?
I mean, I could see putting that together for the odd game or two a year. '
I had the Heaths, and I cracked two Canopies in my IMA box, so I had to buy two Canopies, 4 Leylines of Sanctity, and the rest was maybe $40 bucks?
burn is pretty cheap too
Kor Spiritdancers are I think 5, Coronets are about the same I guess, but I had a couple of each. Bogles are close to five each too but I had 2 already.
Burn is probalby cheaper
minus the guides
[[$goblin guide]]
But it also requires you to know a little more about other decks
not really, you dome them
Bogles and burn playing against each other is always hilarious because game 1 is always 2 ships passing in the night. Unless Bogles has a pregame leyline it's the ultimate hand dump
But yea, Bogles is pretty much the same thing every game: hope you don't draw too many lands and only a couple creatures. The redundancy in that deck rivals tron
Leyline seems to shut down most of Burn, doesn’t it?
They really have no way to deal with that…
pretty much
it kills it
Except try to race with Goblin Guides and Mentors? Which…no…
it isn’t a favorable matchup, no
How do you add custom emoji again?
click on edhrec in the top left
customize slack
I got it. Seems like it's only available on desktop.
Ok. A little off color, but pretty funny.
I get it!
